OL,6,FIt's because of what these women lost
OL,7,Fthat they eventually found each other,
OL,8,FITV News' Chloe Keedy reports
OL,10,FSitting in the middle of the group,
OL,11,Fthere was Tracey Merritt. She was
OL,12,Fwrongly accused by the Post Office of
OL,13,Fstealing #13,500 from her branch in
OL,14,FDorset.
OL,16,FSitting next to Tracey was Jess Kaur,
OL,17,Fa former sub-postmistress from the
OL,18,FWest Midlands. She was accused of
OL,19,Fstealing #11,000 and subsequently
OL,20,Fcharged with 36 counts of theft.
