OL,6,F"It's really nice to connect," Tracey
OL,7,Fexplained. "Because it grounds you
OL,8,Fback and you realise that - you know -
OL,9,Fyou're still not the only one, and
OL,10,Fyou've got that support with each
OL,11,Fother.
OL,13,F"Yes you can talk to your husband, you
OL,14,Fcan talk to your friend, but having
OL,15,Fthis lot... You all understand exactly
OL,16,Fwhat you're going through," Sue
OL,17,FKnight, a former sub-postmistress from
OL,18,FCornwall said.
