OL,3,C'Where is the justice?': Post Office
OL,4,Cvictims on compensation 'cruelty'
OL,6,FThe government says it is working
OL,7,Ftirelessly to provide full, fair and
OL,8,Fswift redress. But 92-year-old Betty
OL,9,FBrown ` the oldest Post Office victim
OL,10,F` is still waiting for hers.
OL,12,F"We have proved we are 100% innocent,"
OL,13,Fshe said. "There's not one person been
OL,14,Fprosecuted and we were victimised and
OL,15,Fare still being victimised. That's
OL,16,Fwhat binds us together."
OL,18,FBetty appealed to the prime minister
OL,19,Fto invite the women to Downing Street.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
